sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant GW as Gateway API<br/>(HTTPRoute)
    participant API as apiserver<br/>8080/TCP HTTP(S)
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant Redis as Redis / Valkey<br/>6379/TCP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Proc as batch-processor<br/>Workers
    participant Inf as llm-d Inference<br/>Gateway
    participant GC as batch-gc

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: Batch Job Submission

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/files (multipart)<br/>Tenant ID: X-MaaS-Username
    GW->>API: Route request
    API->>S3: Upload file content<br/>TLS, AWS credentials
    S3-->>API: Upload confirmed
    API->>PG: Store file metadata<br/>TCP, DSN credentials
    PG-->>API: File record created
    API-->>Client: 200 File object (file_id)

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/batches<br/>Tenant ID: X-MaaS-Username
    GW->>API: Route request
    API->>PG: Create batch record<br/>TCP, DSN credentials
    PG-->>API: Batch created
    API->>Redis: PQEnqueue (priority queue)<br/>TCP, URL credentials
    Redis-->>API: Job enqueued
    API-->>Client: 200 Batch object (batch_id, status=validating)

    Note over Proc,S3: Flow 2: Batch Job Processing

    loop Poll for jobs
        Proc->>Redis: PQDequeue (blocking)<br/>TCP, URL credentials
        Redis-->>Proc: Job payload
    end

    Proc->>PG: Load batch metadata<br/>TCP, DSN credentials
    PG-->>Proc: Batch record
    Proc->>S3: Download input JSONL<br/>TLS, AWS credentials
    S3-->>Proc: Input file stream

    loop For each request in JSONL
        Proc->>Inf: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP(S), Bearer token or mTLS
        Note over Proc,Inf: AIMD concurrency control<br/>Backoff on 429/5xx
        Inf-->>Proc: Inference response
        Proc->>Redis: Update progress counters<br/>TCP, URL credentials
    end

    Proc->>S3: Upload output JSONL<br/>TLS, AWS credentials
    S3-->>Proc: Output file stored
    Proc->>S3: Upload error JSONL (if errors)<br/>TLS, AWS credentials
    Proc->>PG: Update batch status=completed<br/>TCP, DSN credentials

    Note over Client,Redis: Flow 3: Batch Job Cancellation

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/batches/{id}/cancel<br/>Tenant ID: X-MaaS-Username
    GW->>API: Route request
    API->>Redis: PQDelete (remove from queue)<br/>TCP, URL credentials
    API->>Redis: ECProducerSendEvents (cancel event)<br/>TCP, URL credentials
    API->>PG: Update status=cancelling<br/>TCP, DSN credentials
    API-->>Client: 200 Batch (status=cancelling)

    Proc->>Redis: Consume cancel event
    Proc->>S3: Upload partial results<br/>TLS, AWS credentials
    Proc->>PG: Update status=cancelled<br/>TCP, DSN credentials

    Note over GC,S3: Background: Garbage Collection

    loop Every 1h (configurable)
        GC->>PG: Query expired batches/files
        PG-->>GC: Expired items
        GC->>S3: Delete expired file content
        GC->>PG: Delete expired metadata
        GC->>Redis: Clean expired status/queue entries
    end

    loop Every 60m (reconciler)
        GC->>Redis: Check in-flight tracking
        GC->>PG: Find orphaned jobs
        GC->>Redis: Re-enqueue or fail orphans
    end
